<doc id="203938" wikidata="Q154108" url="?curid=203938" title="Milli-">
<text>Milli (symbol m) is a unit prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one thousandth (10−3). Proposed in 1793, and adopted in 1795, the prefix comes from the Latin , meaning &quot;one thousand&quot; (the Latin plural is ). Since 1960, the prefix is part of the International System of Units (SI).

==See also==
* RKM code

