and any twice differentiable scalar function of two real variables and , one has

:formula_72

This immediately implies that is itself an Itô drift-diffusion process.

In higher dimensions, if formula_73 is a vector of Itô processes such that

:formula_74

for a vector formula_75 and matrix formula_76, Itô&#x27;s lemma then states that

:formula_77

where formula_78 is the gradient of w.r.t. , is the Hessian matrix of w.r.t. , and is the trace operator.

=== Poisson jump processes ===
We may also define functions on discontinuous stochastic processes.

Let be the jump intensity. The Poisson process model for jumps is that the probability of one jump in the interval is plus higher order terms. could be a constant, a deterministic function of time, or a stochastic process. The survival probability is the probability that no jump has occurred in the interval . The change in the survival probability is

:formula_79

So

:formula_80

Let be a discontinuous stochastic process. Write formula_81 for the value of &quot;S&quot; as we approach &quot;t&quot; from the left. Write formula_82 for the non-infinitesimal change in as a result of a jump. Then

:formula_83

Let &quot;z&quot; be the magnitude of the jump and let formula_84 be the distribution of &quot;z&quot;. The expected magnitude of the jump is

:formula_85

Define formula_86, a compensated process and martingale, as

