<doc id="204029" wikidata="Q3612617" url="?curid=204029" title="Allodontidae">
<text>Allodontidae (from ancient Greek &quot;ἄλλος&quot; &quot;ὀδούς&quot;, &quot;different tooth&quot;) is a family of extinct multituberculate mammal that lived in what is now North America during the Upper Jurassic period. They were relatively early mammals and are within the informal suborder of &quot;Plagiaulacida&quot;. The family was named by Othniel Charles Marsh in 1889. Two genera are recognized: &quot;Ctenacodon&quot; and &quot;Psalodon&quot;.

== References ==
* Kielan-Jaworowska Z &amp; Hurum JH (2001), &quot;Phylogeny and Systematics of multituberculate mammals&quot;. &quot;Paleontology&quot; 44, p. 389-429.
* Most of this information has been derived from MESOZOIC MAMMALS: Basal Multituberculata, an Internet directory.</text><links>
